value

stringValue

public final java.lang.String stringValue
The string associated with this data dimension. This field is null if the data dimension is numerical (which is most of the time).

Constructor Detail

DataEntry

public DataEntry(double value)
Construct a DataDimension with the specified double value. The stringValue field will be set to null.

Parameters:
value - the double value of this DataDimension

DataEntry

public DataEntry(java.lang.String stringValue,
                 double value)
Construct a DataDimension with the specified string and double values. Usually when this constructor is used, the double value is an ID which corresponds to the string (So if two DataDimensions in the same table have the same string value, they should also have the same double value).

Parameters:
stringValue - the string associated with this data dimension
value - the double value of this DataDimension
Method Detail

toString

public java.lang.String toString()
If the stringValue of this dimension is not null, then it is returned from this method. Otherwise, a string representation of this dimension's double value is returned.
